ork to do, but we're working to get all children out of poverty. We're\ninvesting in a breakfast program�$5&nbsp;million right now�to ensure that\nchildren have breakfast before they go to school.","index":"00204","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We've\ngot a lot of work to do, but our government is moving forward in the right way\nto pull all children out of poverty and to give all people a quality of life in\nManitoba. <i>[interjection]</i> ","index":"00205","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order. ","index":"00206","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr. Mintu\n</b><b><a name=\"_Toc69198458\">Sandhu</a></b><b>�(The\nMaples):</b> Manitoba Public Insurance is in uncharted territory as they have\ncancelled their agreement with Autopac dealers and repair shops.","index":"00207","speaker":"Mintu Sandhu"},{"html":"����� Just\nlike with insurance brokers, the Pallister government is making a mess. Auto\ndealers know that the Pallister government interfered before and are again\nasking for a conciliator.� ","index":"00208","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Will\nthe minister be doing so for auto dealers? Yes or no? <i>[interjection]</i>� ","index":"00209","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order. ","index":"00210","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Jeff\n</b><b><a name=\"_Toc69198459\">Wharton</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Crown Services):</b> Certainly, on this side of the House we respect the\nprocess, Madam Speaker. We respect that the Automotive Trades Association and\nthe Manitoba Motor Dealers Association are working with MPI for the betterment\nof all Manitobans. ","index":"00211","speaker":"Jeff Wharton"},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable member for The&nbsp;Maples, on a supplementary\nquestion. ","index":"00212","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nSandhu:</b> Automotive trades are now seeking a court injunction against MPI.\nThey are asking for a conciliator just like what IBAM got. ","index":"00213","speaker":"Mintu Sandhu"},{"html":"����� We\nknow that acti