what this government is about. ","index":"00261","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon. Jon </b><b><a name=\"_Toc69198470\">Gerrard</a></b><b>�(River Heights):</b> Home care should be the first option for seniors\nwho need it. Important steps to facilitate it�facilitate this are, first, to\nensure shut-in seniors can receive the vaccine in their home and, second, to\nimprove access to self-managed care. ","index":"00262","speaker":"Jon Gerrard"},{"html":"����� Right\nnow, the self-managed care program is confusing and too many seniors are being\ntreated with hostility and resentment for wanting to use it, and they are being\ndeterred from using it. ","index":"00263","speaker":""},{"html":"����� When\nwill the Minister of Health act to make sure that the self-managed care program\nis working more smoothly and is adequately resourced to ensure more seniors can\ncontinue to live in their own home instead of having to move to a\nlong-term-care home? ","index":"00264","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nHeather </b><b><a name=\"_Toc69198471\">Stefanson</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Health and Seniors Care):</b> Well, Madam Speaker, we certainly agree with\nthat approach. We want to ensure that we find ways for seniors to remain in\ntheir homes as long as possible with their loved ones. ","index":"00265","speaker":"Heather Stefanson"},{"html":"����� And\ncertainly we recognize that and we are working with Shared Health, with the regional\nhealth authorities, to ensure that we put together a plan to ensure that that\ntakes place, Madam Speaker.","index":"00266","speaker":""},{"html":"����� With\nrespect, the member opposite mentioned the&nbsp;&nbsp;COVID vaccine, getting it\nout to as many communities as possible. That's what we have been doing, with\nrespect to our pop-up clinics, as well as our FIT teams, Madam Speaker. ","index":"00267","speaker":""},{"html":"����� We'll\ncontinue to work with those to ensure that we have greater access to all\nManitobans, who need, want and deserve the